OL,3,CFertility rate in England and Wales
OL,4,Cdrops to new record low
OL,6,FWhile the numbers of live births
OL,7,Facross the two nations has also fallen
OL,8,Fto its lowest in five decades.
OL,10,FAmong the groups most impacted are
OL,11,Famong women aged 20-24 with rates down
OL,12,F79% from 181.6 live births per 1,000
OL,13,Fwomen in 1964 to 38.6 in 2023. While
OL,14,Fthe average age of new mothers
OL,15,Fremained the same, the average age of
OL,16,Ffathers increased from 33.7 in 2022 to
OL,17,F33.8 last year.
