OL,3,CFertility rate in England and Wales
OL,4,Cdrops to new record low
OL,6,FThe regions experiencing the biggest
OL,7,Fdrops in overall fertility were Wales
OL,8,F(1.46 to 1.39) and North West England
OL,9,F(1.53 to 1.46) followed by London
OL,10,F(1.39 to 1.35). The North East and
OL,11,FWest Midlands experienced the smallest
OL,12,Fdecreases out of all the regions.
OL,14,FAccording to the ONS, the fertility
OL,15,Frate is defined by the average number
OL,16,Fof children a group of women would
OL,17,Fhave if they experienced the age-
OL,18,Fspecific fertility rates throughout
OL,19,Ftheir childbearing life.
